msg: A binary file is a file that cannot be parsed in ascii and must not be
transformed.  A text file is a file that can be viewed and manipulated
by any run of the mill text editor, can pass in and out of cvs with the
Commit then review means that you propose code changes by demonstrating
them to the tree.  This does -not- apply to major cvs changes, mass symbol
name changes or editing the repository.  The -kb change is vetoed.
